### Static vs. Dynamic Context

| Context Type    | Description                                                                                   | Analogous Concept                        |
|-----------------|-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------|-----------------------------------------|
| **Static Context**  | Always loaded core project information that never changes (e.g., "agents.mmd" file with project rules). | Essential survival gear (tent, water).  |
| **Dynamic Context** | Information loaded only on demand when needed, implemented via **agent skills** for modular task execution.         | Specific topographical map pulled out at critical points on a hike. |

**Key insight:** Overloading AI with full project context causes **context rot**, where the model’s attention is diluted and output quality degrades. Dynamic context loading counters this by delivering relevant information precisely when needed.

