### The 80% Problem and Human Role

- AI handles roughly **80% of the routine, boilerplate, and structural code**.
- Humans focus on the remaining **20% of complex, domain-specific logic, edge cases, and strategic decisions**.
- This reframes AI's impact from job replacement to **automation of tedious work, freeing developers to concentrate on higher-value architectural judgment and verification**.
- True effectiveness comes from mastering this balance, not from blind code acceptance.

